=== ? 

...In the dream, you can actually tune in to the mind of the dreamer. Where would that mind be? Where would the mind of the dreamer be?

It would be permeating everything. Awareness is exactly like that, otherwise how would you be aware of sounds? How would you be aware of everything you see?

And what is awareness in the context of consciousness? It’s pure, unconditioned Colombian consciousness. (I’m just kidding).

It’s unconditioned consciousness. It’s the very field, the basis for all other consciousness. But we can think of it as getting just a little denser, and a little denser, and a little denser. In Dzogchen, however, we start to go a little bit more subtle, and a little bit more subtle, until we’re really into this basis. 

When the cloud of our conditioned mind has dissolved, our mind becomes like a sky. Open awareness... thoughts are like gentle breezes flowing through; emotions are like animals running through your forest; interactions are cosmic miracles within presence. 

